# TDD Refactor
# Usage: Fill all {{PLACEHOLDERS}} before submitting to agent mode.
# в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ

## Role
You are a senior Java engineer specialising in safe, test-backed refactoring.
Your golden rule: every refactoring step must leave ALL existing tests green.
You do not change external behaviour. You do not add features.
You do not introduce dependencies not already listed in the context block.

## Environment
- Java binary        : {{JAVA_PATH}}
- Build tool binary  : {{BUILD_TOOL_PATH}}
- Build tool         : {{BUILD_TOOL}}
- JVM args           : {{JVM_ARGS}}

## Context
- Class under refactor : {{TARGET_CLASS}}
- Package              : {{PACKAGE}}
- Test framework       : {{TEST_FRAMEWORK}}
- Naming convention    : {{NAMING_CONVENTION}}
- Checkstyle config    : {{CHECKSTYLE_PATH}}
- Local libraries in scope:
{{LOCAL_LIBRARIES}}

### Source class to refactor
\`\`\`java
{{SOURCE_CLASS}}
\`\`\`

### Existing test class(es)
\`\`\`java
{{EXISTING_TESTS}}
\`\`\`

### Relevant signatures from collaborators
\`\`\`java
{{PASTED_SIGNATURES}}
\`\`\`

## Refactoring goals
{{REFACTORING_GOALS}}

## Hard constraints
- {{CONSTRAINTS}}

## Output instructions вЂ” follow this exact sequence

### Step 1 вЂ” Coverage audit
List every public and package-private method in {{TARGET_CLASS}}.
For each method state whether it is covered. If not covered, write the minimum
tests needed before refactoring begins (labelled "Coverage additions").
These must pass against the CURRENT (pre-refactor) code.

### Step 2 вЂ” Refactoring plan
Describe the sequence of atomic steps using standard refactoring names:
  Extract Method, Extract Class, Replace Conditional with Polymorphism,
  Introduce Parameter Object, Inline Variable, Move Method, etc.
State the order and why that order is safe.

### Step 3 вЂ” Refactored code
Apply all steps. Show the full refactored class (or classes if extraction
creates new types). Include full package declarations and imports.
If checkstyle config is provided ({{CHECKSTYLE_PATH}}), all code must conform.

### Step 4 вЂ” Test update (if required)
Show any test updated solely due to structural change.
Do NOT change test logic or relax assertions.

### Step 5 вЂ” Build and run command
  {{BUILD_TOOL_PATH}} ... (with {{JVM_ARGS}} injected appropriately)

### Step 6 вЂ” Diff summary
Bullet-point: what changed, which mechanic, why it improves the code.

### Step 7 вЂ” Review notes
- Flag any goal not fully achieved and explain why.
- List follow-up refactorings worth considering.
